Example
Return the entire URL of the current page:

Copy
let x = location.href;

Description
The href property gets and sets the entire URL of the current page.

Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
href	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Return the href property:

Copy
let a = location.href;
Set the href property:

Copy
location.href = URL;
Property Values
Value	Type	Description
URL	String	the URL of the link.
Return Value
A String, representing the entire URL of the page, including the protocol (like http://).

More Examples
Set the href value to point to another web site:

Copy
location.href = "https://www.demo2s.com";

Example
Set the href value to point to an anchor within a page:

Copy
location.href = "#top";

Example
Set the href value to point to an email address, will open and create a new email message:

Copy
location.href = "mailto:someone@example.com";
